main event: A civilian witness spotted an unidentified object near Holly, Florida on April 4, 1966.
interesting points: The object was round in shape with a flared end, and was approximately 6 feet long and 2.5 feet high.
The object had 6 round ports on the blunt end and 4 square ports on the flared end.
As the witness reached out to touch the object, it ascended quickly and emitted a high-pitched sound.
The object rose to an elevation of 80-100 feet and then moved rapidly to the west, disappearing almost instantaneously.
The witness reported almost calm weather conditions with light rain and fog at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: a round object with a flared end
